Cape Town – A picture of former Zimbabwean president Robert Mugabe and his wife Grace purportedly watching the inauguration of Emmerson Mnangagwa as president of the country on Friday has gone viral on social media. In the picture, the Mugabes are dressed in black and as one social media user @KayodeAjulo says, Grace's "facial expression says a lot".  See the picture and the reaction from various social media users below Longtime deputy Emmerson Mnangagwa, fired by Mugabe earlier this month, was sworn in on Friday after making a triumphant return to the country.  Mnangagwa praised outgoing leader Mugabe as "the father of the nation" during his inauguration address. "Let me at this stage pay tribute to one of the, and the only surviving, founding fathers of our nation, comrade Robert Gabriel Mugabe," Mnangagwa said in front of a crowd of tens of thousands at his inauguration ceremony. "Let us all accept and acknowledge his immense contribution to the building of our nation." 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  